---
import LegalLayout from '../components/LegalLayout.astro';
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Designed to Elevate handles personal information collected through this website and during client engagements."
  pathname="privacy"
  intro="This page explains what information Designed to Elevate collects, how it is used, and the third-party services involved in operating this site."
>
  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    Designed to Elevate is a one-person web design and lead-system studio operated by Bill Chicha and based in
    Ohio. References to "we," "us," and "our" on this page refer to Designed to Elevate. Contact information is
    listed at the bottom of this policy and in the site footer.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>
    When you submit the contact form, we collect the information you provide — typically your name, business
    name, email address, phone number, website URL, and any details you share about your project.
  </p>
  <p>
    Standard server logs may collect basic technical information such as browser type, device, IP address,
    referring page, and pages visited. This is used to understand site usage and improve the site.
  </p>

  <h2>How we use information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to your inquiry and provide a quote</li>
    <li>To deliver services you have engaged us to perform</li>
    <li>To communicate about active projects and follow-ups</li>
    <li>To improve the website and services</li>
    <li>To meet legal, accounting, and tax obligations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    The site is built and operated using the following third-party services. Each handles a specific piece of
    site functionality and may receive limited information about your visit or your contact-form submission:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Vercel</strong> — hosts and serves the website. Vercel processes server logs (IP address, request
      metadata) as part of normal hosting operations. See
      <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Vercel's privacy policy</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Web3Forms</strong> — processes contact-form submissions and forwards them to our email. Form data
      you submit (name, business, email, phone, website, message) passes through Web3Forms' service before
      reaching us. See
      <a href="https://web3forms.com/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Web3Forms' privacy policy</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Google Fonts</strong> — serves the typefaces used on this site. Google may receive your IP address
      and basic browser information when fonts load. See
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's privacy policy</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We may add or change service providers over time (for example, switching the contact-form processor).
    This list will be updated when that happens.
  </p>

  <h2>Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell personal information. We share information only with the service providers listed above, only
    to the extent necessary to operate the site and respond to your inquiry, and only under reasonable
    confidentiality expectations.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We use <strong>Google Analytics (GA4)</strong> and <strong>Google Ads conversion tracking</strong> to
    measure website traffic and the performance of our advertising. These services may set cookies and receive
    your IP address, device and browser information, and the pages and actions you take on the site (including
    submitting the quote form). We use this only to understand site usage and to see which ads lead to
    enquiries — we do not sell your information. See
    <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's privacy policy</a>,
    and you can opt out using the
    <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on</a>.
    Our hosting provider may also set technical cookies needed to serve and secure the site. Your browser
    controls cookie behavior through its settings.
  </p>

  <h2>Your choices</h2>
  <p>
    You can request access, correction, or deletion of personal information you have provided by emailing us
    at <a href="mailto:bilsonxnc@gmail.com">bilsonxnc@gmail.com</a>. We will respond within a reasonable time.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    The site and services are not directed to children under 13 and we do not knowingly collect personal
    information from them.
  </p>

  <h2>Updates to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. The effective date in the page header will reflect the most
    recent revision. Material changes will be reflected in the policy text rather than communicated separately.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy can be sent to
    <a href="mailto:bilsonxnc@gmail.com">bilsonxnc@gmail.com</a>
    or by phone at <a href="tel:+17406176488">(740) 617-6488</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
